In order to avoid the issuance of suspension orders to contractors and ensure that infrastructure projects are completed on time, we recommended that management:

a)	conduct detailed engineering investigations including right of way acquisitions before the conduct of bidding and award of contract for infrastructure projects;

b)	consider the topography of the region, weather condition and prevalence of typhoons thereat in the determination of the contract time and the period of project implementation;

c).	issue suspension orders to contractors only when necessary and the notice to resume work should be issued immediately after the reason for the suspension of work has been resolved.

d).	avoid the implementation of another project that may cause delay to the completion of on-going project such as concreting of road going to the project site.

